'''Abū Zayd ibn Muḥammad ibn Abī Zayd''' (active c. 1186 — 1219, [[Kashan]]; often simply referred to as '''Abu Zayd''') was a medieval Persian potter. His extant signed body of work, 15 pieces, is larger than that of any other medieval Iranian potter.<ref>[http://www.oxfordartonline.com/subscriber/article/grove/art/T000296 "Abu Zayd."] In Grove Art Online. Oxford Art Online, (accessed February 5, 2012; subscription required).</ref>
