{{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = <!--{{PAGENAME}} by default--> | synonym = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | pronounce = | specialty = <!-- from Wikidata, can be overwritten --> | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }} '''Vaginal melanoma''' is a rare [[malignancy]] that originates from [[Melanocyte|melanocytes]] in the [[vaginal epithelium]]. It is also known as a [[melanocytic tumor]] or as a malignant [[melanoma]].<ref name="atlas">{{cite web|title=Vulva and Vagina tumors: an overview|url=http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Tumors/VulVaginaCarcID5274.html|website=atlasgeneticsoncology.org}}</ref> It is aggressive and infrequently cured. The five year survival rate is approximately 21%.<ref name=":2" /> It was first described in 1887 and only 500 cases are found in current literature. Vaginal melanoma is 3% of all [[Vaginal cancer|vaginal cancers]] and only 0.3% of all melanomas. When the neoplasm is discovered it has already become invasive and prognosis is poor.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Kalampokas E, Kalampokas T, Damaskos C | title = Primary Vaginal Melanoma, A Rare and Aggressive Entity. A Case Report and Review of the Literature | journal = In Vivo | volume = 31 | issue = 1 | pages = 133–139 | date = January 2017 | pmid = 28064232 | doi = 10.21873/invivo.11036 | url = http://iv.iiarjournals.org/content/31/1/133 | pmc = 5354139 }}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=miALDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA41&dq=Vagina+cyst&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi0v46b_drZAhUJSN8KHXARAWoQ6AEILzAB#v=onepage&q=Vagina%20cyst&f=false|title=Essentials of Gynecologic Pathology|last=Dey|first=Pranab|date=2017-02-06|publisher=JP Medical Ltd|year=|isbn=9789386261205|location=|pages=47|language=en}}</ref> The average age of those diagnosed is sixty-years-old.<ref name=":2" /> ==Presentation== This cancer most often develops on the lowest third of the vagina. It is darkly pigmented and of an irregular shape. Melanoma of the vagina can be as large as severally centimeters in size.<ref name=":2" /> ==Histology== When the tissue is assessed, the histological characteristics include: * the shape of the cells appear similar to epithelial and spindle-shaped * the growth occurs in the shapes of sheets and nests * the presence of [[melanin]] in the cells * the nucleus of the cells is large and abnormal<ref name=":2" /> ===Other cancers=== Other cancerous conditions arise from vaginal epithelium:<ref name=":1">{{cite journal|vauthors=Chen L, Xiong Y, Wang H, Liang L, Shang H, Yan X|date=October 2014|title=Malignant melanoma of the vagina: A case report and review of the literature|journal=Oncology Letters|volume=8|issue=4|pages=1585–1588|doi=10.3892/ol.2014.2357|pmc=4156219|pmid=25202372}}</ref> * [[Vaginal squamous-cell carcinoma]] arises from the [[squamous cell]]s of the vaginal epithelium<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cancer.gov/types/vaginal/patient/vaginal-treatment-pdq|title=Vaginal Cancer Treatment|website=National Cancer Institute|language=en|access-date=2018-02-08}}</ref> * [[Vaginal adenocarcinoma]] arises from secretory cells in the vaginal epithelium<ref name=":0" /> * [[Clear cell adenocarcinoma of the vagina]] this malignancy arises in some women prenatally exposed to [[diethylstilbestrol]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/DES/consumers/about/index.html|title=About DES|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=February 8, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/des/consumers/about/effects_daughters.html|title=Known Health Effects for DES Daughters|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=February 8, 2018}}</ref>
